  <abstract>This report provides a new look at a previous report of the same name published in 1988, which showed that young families with children in 1986 were far worse off economically than the previous generation. New data collected shows that young families with children were barely helped at all by the economic growth of the mid-to late 1980s, and that the tiny gains they achieved during this period were more than wiped out in 1990 by the effects of the Recession.</abstract>
